I only met him a few times but each time, his smile lit up the room. ✨ I was a massive fan…from the first day I watched him on SYTYCD.  Joy and talent exuded from him and seeing him do his thing in person was such a treat…especially when he was on stage with his equally joyful and talented wife, @allisonholker . 
Since hearing the news, I can’t stop thinking that you just never know how someone is hurting behind closed doors and how we can all be better…myself included. So, if you’re hurting, share your pain with someone you trust or call/text the National Suicide & Crisis Lifeline at 988.  If you think someone is hurting, reach out and offer an ear or a shoulder or the strength to call 988 for them. If you think it’s funny to say “go kill yourself” to your friends, it’s not even close to funny (I just heard from a friend that this is a thing amongst teens). Words matter. Actions matter. Do better. Be better. 
My heart breaks for Allison, his family and friends and anyone who was touched by his brilliant light. @sir_twitch_alot , you will be incredibly missed. 💔 
#riptwitch #gonetoosoon

On my 50th bday trip, @jason_tartick asked me what the secret to happiness in my life was (or something like that 🤪) and  at first, I said “love”. It was an easy answer and definitely a big part of why I have such deep smile lines. BUT, when I thought deeper into the question, I realized that more than anything else, my life’s happiness comes through connection. Connection to the love of my life and the family we created out of that love. ❤️Connection to lifelong friends and my village in Vail with whom I’m grateful to do life with. Connection to family friends and those who have shown me kindness. Connection to work friends who help me put those good ol brain muscles to use. 😜Connection to fans and producers, executives and crew who helped me find my future. Connection to teachers and coaches who help guide my (not really) babies (anymore), and my community relationships that help me feel like I’m not alone and am making a difference. 
I’ve heard a lot of people talk about setting a word of the year instead of a resolution. If you haven’t already guessed, mine is connection.  Appreciating the connections at present and putting in the effort to create more. 
Thank you to those who helped me find happiness in 2022 and HAPPY NEW YEAR! 
#day1to365 #happynewyear #grateful

As a new mom, I worried a LOT. 🥺 Was my baby boy getting enough milk or food or oxygen (high altitude!)? Was he dry and warm, well-rested, happy and healthy?? 😬
15 years later, my worries have drastically changed from his basic survival to that plus everything else! 
Does he know how to cope with the hormonal wave that is teenage life?
Is he doing well enough in school to get into a good college…if that’s what he wants to do?! 
When is he ever going to get enough hours to get his license? Will he stay safe behind the wheel?! 
Do his coaches and teachers see him as the quiet introvert that he is or a standoffish punk with a chip on his shoulder? 
Is he respectful? 
Does he make good choices? 
Does he know how much he is loved?! 
SO many worries and SO much heavier than the days of my tiny peanut with a binky in his mouth. 
One thing that I have high hopes of conquering is his unfortunate bout with acne. Add together hockey and lacrosse helmets, constant hat-wearing, teenage stress, hormones and oily skin, his face is under attack. But yesterday was Day 1 of our retaliation, thanks to @aviclear ! As a patient at @vitahlmed in Denver, I found out about this new laser by @cuterainc that treats acne without having to take a pill or fill a prescription. He’ll do 3 treatments in total, and may deal with a “purge” right after but other than being more dry than usual, there’s no downtime! I’m excited to share our journey with all of you out there who deal with acne or have a kiddo like mine who does. It takes a village and aim thankful that mine includes @aviclear .  #acnetreatment 
#prescriptionfree #chemicalfree 
#byeacne

It’s shocking to me how many things we still don’t openly talk about these days. I’m excited to be a #TENApartner and encourage a dialogue around our ever evolving bodies, especially as it relates to menopause and incontinence. Literally all women go through menopause, but somehow when we reach that moment in our lives, we just have no clue because no one around us is talking about it. 
 
Case in point – bladder leakage, a common symptom during menopause – affects 1 in 3 women in North America, yet it takes 6 to 8 years for women to bring the topic up with their doctors. That’s a pretty crazy stat and I know that the more we talk about it, the less taboo it’s going to be, and the more women will feel comfortable seeking help. 
 
Thank you again @TENAusa for bringing me along on this #MyEvolvingBody journey and for making quality products that prioritize intimate skin health. I can’t wait to share more!

I love birthdays. 💯 Celebrating the people in my life actually feels selfish, though. If it goes well, we laugh and smile and connect and who wouldn’t want that?! Well, probably my husband. Not the laugh and smile and connect part…but the attention. 
It’s his 49th birthday today and I asked him if he wanted anything.  All the things that I know would help ease his stress (and mine!) these days aren’t things that I can magically bring to life, or buy at Target:

* A cure from Lyme disease and it’s co-infections 👎🏼

* A winning lottery ticket so we can keep our house in the mountains and buy a home near our kids new school. 👎🏼

* A real estate market that would allow buyers to avoid astronomical interest rates and take over ownership of a house that we’ve truly loved for 20 years because we made a decision to invest in our kids and their future. 👎🏼

The one thing that I could pretty much guarantee that would make him happy was spending time on his bike and with his fur bestie in the mountains.  So that’s how he started his day. They’ll always be his home, no matter if our address is there, but he’ll always be mine. ❤️

So, even though I bought balloons and he’ll get cards and presents and love via social media posts and at our family dinner tonight I hope that the warm fuzzies outweigh the dislike of attention and he knows how deeply we love him…how deeply I love him, and always will. 

Happy birthday babe. 😘❤️🥳

#happy49th #happybirthdaymylove
